com.datumbox.common.dataobjects

Class FlatDataList

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.datumbox.common.dataobjects.DataStructure<T>
      • com.datumbox.common.dataobjects.DataStructureCollection<T>
        • com.datumbox.common.dataobjects.DataStructureList<List<Object>>
          • com.datumbox.common.dataobjects.FlatDataList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<Object>

    public final class FlatDataList
extends DataStructureList<List<Object>>
implements Iterable<Object>
    The FlatDataList is a data structure that stores internally a List<Object>. The class provides a set of useful methods to access and modify the contents of the collection.
    Author:
    Vasilis Vryniotis
    See Also:
